   SPEEDING-DRIVERS (Hartford, Conn.) _ Early last week, Mathew
Hennessy, mild-mannered computer programmer, was driving toward
Manhattan at 100 mph. He is one of a growing number of American
drivers who, according to traffic experts, are pushing highway
speeds to new heights. Steering bigger and more powerful cars and
exploiting increasingly lax police enforcement, more drivers than
ever are treating speed limits as suggestions, experts say. By Paul
Zielbauer. (With photo.)
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move the story by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
