   (NYT13) YONKERS, N.Y. -- Dec. 26, 1999 -- SPEEDING-DRIVERS --
Early last week, Mathew Hennessy, mild-mannered computer
programmer, was driving toward Manhattan at 100 mph. He is one of a
growing number of American drivers who, according to traffic
experts, are pushing highway speeds to new heights. Steering bigger
and more powerful cars and exploiting increasingly lax police
enforcement, more drivers than ever are treating speed limits as
suggestions, experts say. (Joyce Dopkeen/The New York Times)
</P>
