   (NYT18) BRIDGEWATER, N.J. -- Dec. 26, 1999 --
NEWEST-IMMIGRANTS-4 -- Turkey and shrimp with steamed sweet rice as
prepared, from left, by Sharon Wang, Susan Lin and Sharon's mother,
Chunting Chai. In the southwestern sections of Bridgewater, the
last decade has seen farms and woods give way to 3,000 houses in
glistening subdivisions. As many as half the residents in some
neighborhoods are Asian, led by Indians, Chinese and Filipinos.
(Dith Pran/The New York Times)
