   (NYT10) WASHINGTON -- Dec. 26, 1999 -- PATENTS -- In a highly
unusual move, Todd Dickinson, the Patents Commissioner, ordered the
re-examination of a patent. Though rare, such an action usually
results in the patent being revoked. The move was widely praised.
(The New York Times)
</P>
